\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 11. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 You have emulated the hated Esau, my soul, and have given up your birthright of pristine beauty to your 
supplanter, and you have lost your father's blessing, and have been tripped up twice in action and knowledge. Therefore, O wretch, repent now}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 . ( Genesis 25:31; 27:37)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 12. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 Esau was called Edom for his extreme passion of madness for women. For ever burning
 with incontinence and stained with pleasures, he was named Edom, which means a red-hot sin-loving soul. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (Genesis 25:30) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 13. . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 Have you heard of Job who was made holy on a dunghill, O my soul? You have not emulated his courage, nor had his firmness of pu
rpose in all you have learned or known, or in your temptations, but you have proved unpersevering. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (Job 1) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 14. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
He who was formerly on a throne is now naked on a dunghill and covered with sores. He who had many children and was much admired is suddenly childless and homeless. Yet he regarded the dunghill as a palace and his sores as pearls. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (Job 2:7-8) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 15. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
The opulent and righteous man, arrayed in royal dignity, crown and purple, abounding in wealth and cattle, was suddenly shorn of his riches, glory and kingdom and became a beggar. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 16. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
If he who was righteous and blameless beyond all did not escape the snares and nets of the deceiver, what will you do, my soul, who are sin-loving and wretched, if something unexpected happens to you? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 17. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 My body is de
