\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs36\i\f1\fs24\cf6\insrsid12938973 Eirmos}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs35\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid12938973 
We have sinned, transgressed, done wrong before Thee, we have not watched or done as Thou hast commanded us. But do not give us up utterly, O God of our Fathers. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs36\i\f1\fs24\cf6\insrsid12938973 Refrain:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs35\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid12938973 Have mercy on me, O God, have mercy on me.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs36\i\f1\fs24\cf6\insrsid12938973 Troparia:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 1. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
I have sinned, offended and rejected Thy commandment, for I have advanced in sins and added wounds to my sores. But in Thy compassion have mercy on me, O God of our Fathers. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 2. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
I have confessed to Thee, my Judge, the secrets of my heart. See my humility, see also my distress, and attend to my judgment now. And in Thy compassion have mercy on me, O God of our Fathers. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 3. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 When Saul of old lost his father's asses, besides getting 
news of them he incidentally found a kingdom. But watch, my soul, lest without noticing it, you prefer your animal cravings to the Kingdom of Christ. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (I Kings 10:2)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 4. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 If David, the father of our Divine Lord, doubly sinned of old, my soul, when he was pi
erced with the arrow of adultery and struck with the spear of remorse for murder, yet you have a sickness graver than deeds in your will and appetites. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (II Kings 11; 12:1-23) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 5. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 David once joined sin to sin, for he mixed adultery with murder, yet he imme
diately offered double repentance. But you, my soul, have done things more wicked without repenting to God. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 6. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
David of old composed a song, painting it as in a picture by which he exposes the deed he had done, crying: Have mercy on me, for against Thee only have I sinned, Who art God of all. Cleanse me. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (Psalm 50)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 7. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
When the Ark was being carried on a wagon, and when one of the oxen slipped, Uzzah only touched it and experienced the wrath of God. But avoid, my soul, his presumption and truly reverence divine things. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (II Kings 6:6)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 8. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 You have heard of Absalom, how h
e rose against nature. You know his accursed deeds and how he insulted the bed of his father David. But you have imitated his passionate and pleasure-loving cravings. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (II Kings 15; 16:21)}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 9. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 You have enslaved your free dignity to your body, my soul, for 
you have found in Satan another Ahitophel and have consented to his counsels. But Christ Himself scattered them, that you may at all events be saved. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (II Kings 16:20)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 10. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 Wonderful Solomon, who was full of the grace of wisdom, at one time did evil in God
's sight and fell away from Him. And you, my soul, have resembled him by your accursed life. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (III Kings 11; Ecclus 47:12-20) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 11. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 Carried away by the pleasure of his passions, he defiled himself. Alas, the lover of wisdom is a lover of loose women and est
ranged from God! And you, my soul, have in mind imitated him by your shameful pleasures. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (III Kings 3:12; 11:4-12) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 12. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
You, my soul, have rivaled Rehoboam who would not listen to his father's advisors, and that vicious slave Jeroboam the apostate of old. But shun such mimicry and cry to God: I have sinned, have compassion on me}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 .(III Kings 12:13. -20) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 13. . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
You have rivaled Ahab in defilements, my soul. Alas, you have been a lodging-place of fleshly pollutions and a shameful vessel of passions. But groan from your depths and tell God your sins. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 
(III Kings 16:30) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 14. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
Elijah once burned a hundred of Jezebel's flunkeys when he had destroyed her shameful prophets as a proof and rebuke for Ahab. But avoid imitating these two, my soul, and master yourself. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (I
V Kings 1:10-15; III Kings 18:40)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 15. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
Heaven is closed to you, my soul, and the famine of God has reached you, for you have been disobedient as was Ahab of old to the words of Elijah the Tishbite. But be like the woman of Sarepta, and feed the Prophet's soul. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (III Kings 17) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 16. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
You have piled up sins like Manasseh by deliberate choice, my soul, setting up your passions as idols and multiplying abominations. But now fervently emulate his repentance and acquire compunction. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (IV Kings 21; II Chronicles 33) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 17. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
I fall down before Thee and bring Thee as tears my words: I have sinned like the harlot, and transgressed as no other on earth. But have compassion, O Lord, on Thy work, and recall me. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 18. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 I have buried Thy image and broken Thy commandment. All my
 beauty is darkened and my lamp is extinguished by my passions, O Savior. But have compassion and restore to me, as David sings, joy. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (Psalm 50:14)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 19. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 Return, repent, uncover what is hidden. Say to God Who knows everything: Thou knowest my secrets, O on
ly Savior; but have mercy on me, as David sings, according to Thy mercy. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 (Psalm 50)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 20. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
My days have vanished like a dream on waking. Therefore I weep on my bed like Hezekiah that years may be added to my life. But what Isaiah will come to you, my soul, except the God of all? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs38\f1\fs16\insrsid12938973 
(IV Kings 20:3; Isaiah 38:2) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs36\i\f1\fs24\cf6\insrsid12938973 Refrain:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs35\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid12938973 Holy mother Mary, pray for us.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs36\i\f1\fs24\cf6\insrsid12938973 To St. Mary of Egypt: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
By crying to the immaculate Mother of God, thou didst repel the rage of passions which once violently harassed thee, and didst put to shame the enemy tempter. But now grant me, thy servant, also help out of trouble. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs36\i\f1\fs24\cf6\insrsid12938973 Refrain:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs35\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid12938973 Holy mother Mary, pray for us.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs36\i\f1\fs24\cf6\insrsid12938973 To St. Mary of Egypt: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
He Whom thou lovest, He Whom thou desirest, He on Whose track thou camest, mother, found thee and granted thee repentance, for He is God Who alone is compassionate. Implore Him unceasingly to deliver us from passions and adversities. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs36\i\f1\fs24\cf6\insrsid12938973 Refrain:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs35\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid12938973 Holy father Andrew, pray for us.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs36\i\f1\fs24\cf6\insrsid12938973 To St. Andrew of Crete:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973 
 Strengthen me on the rock of faith by thy intercessions, O father, and wall and fortify me with an awed sense of the divine indwelling, and grant me repentance, O Andrew, now. And I 
implore thee to deliver me from the snares of foes actively seeking my life. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs35\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid12938973 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs36\i\f1\fs24\cf6\insrsid12938973 To The Trinity:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  O Trinity simple and undivided, of one essence and one nature, Lights and Light, three Holies and 
one Holy, God the Trinity is hymned. But sing, my soul, and glorify the Life and Lives, the God of all. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs35\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid12938973 Now and ever, and to the ages of ages. Amen.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs36\i\f1\fs24\cf6\insrsid12938973 Theotokion:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs37\f1\fs32\insrsid12938973  We sing of thee, we bless thee, we worship thee, O Mother of God, for thou gavest birth to 
one of the inseparable Trinity, the one Son and God, and to us on earth thou hast opened the heavenly realms. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12938973 
\par 
